### 2. `.gitignore`

Create a `.gitignore` file in the root directory of your project. This file ensures that certain files and directories are not tracked by Git.

```plaintext
# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
env/
venv/
.idea/
*.db
*.sqlite3

# Node.js
node_modules/
build/
dist/
.env

# Logs
logs/
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# OS-specific
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IDEs
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo